<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Adaptive Learning V2 — Grades 1–6</title>
  <style>
    :root{--bg:#0f172a;--panel:#111827;--panel2:#1f2937;--text:#f8fafc;--muted:#cbd5e1;--accent:#22c55e;--accent2:#60a5fa;--warn:#f59e0b;--bad:#ef4444;--good:#10b981;--chip:#334155;--border:#374151}
    *{box-sizing:border-box} body{margin:0;font-family:Inter,system-ui,-apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,Arial,sans-serif;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#020617,#0f172a 35%,#111827);color:var(--text);min-height:100vh}
    .wrap{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px}.card{background:rgba(17,24,39,.96);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:22px;padding:20px;box-shadow:0 18px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.28);margin-bottom:18px}
    h1,h2,h3{margin:0 0 12px} h1{font-size:2rem} h2{font-size:1.35rem} h3{font-size:1.05rem} p{color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55}
    label{display:block;font-weight:700;margin:10px 0 6px} input,select,button,textarea{font:inherit;border-radius:14px;border:1px solid var(--border)} input,select{width:100%;padding:12px 14px;background:#0b1220;color:var(--text)}
    button{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--accent2),#8b5cf6);color:white;padding:12px 18px;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-weight:800;transition:.18s transform ease,.18s opacity ease} button:hover{transform:translateY(-1px)}
    button.secondary{background:#1e293b;border:1px solid var(--border)} button.ghost{background:transparent;border:1px solid var(--border)}
    .row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(12,1fr);gap:14px}.col-3{grid-column:span 3}.col-4{grid-column:span 4}.col-6{grid-column:span 6}.col-8{grid-column:span 8}.col-12{grid-column:span 12}
    @media (max-width:800px){.col-3,.col-4,.col-6,.col-8,.col-12{grid-column:span 12}} .pill{display:inline-block;padding:6px 10px;border-radius:999px;background:var(--chip);color:#e2e8f0;font-size:.84rem;margin:4px 6px 0 0}
    .topbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:14px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap}.hidden{display:none !important}.progress{height:14px;border-radius:999px;background:#0b1220;border:1px solid var(--border);overflow:hidden}
    .progress>div{height:100%;width:0;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--accent),var(--accent2));transition:width .25s ease}.choice{display:block;width:100%;text-align:left;padding:14px 16px;margin:10px 0;background:#0b1220;color:var(--text);border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:16px}
    .choice:hover{border-color:#60a5fa}.choice.selected{outline:2px solid #60a5fa;border-color:#60a5fa}.feedback{border-radius:18px;padding:16px;margin-top:14px;border:1px solid var(--border)}.feedback.good{background:rgba(16,185,129,.12);border-color:rgba(16,185,129,.4)}.feedback.bad{background:rgba(239,68,68,.1);border-color:rgba(239,68,68,.35)}
    .stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:12px}@media (max-width:800px){.stats{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}} .stat{background:#0b1220;border:1px solid var(--border);padding:14px;border-radius:18px}.stat .big{font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800}
    .mini{background:#0b1220;border:1px solid var(--border);padding:12px;border-radius:16px}.review-item{border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:18px;padding:14px;margin:10px 0;background:#0b1220}.good-text{color:#6ee7b7}.bad-text{color:#fca5a5}.muted{color:var(--muted)} table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse} th,td{padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);text-align:left;vertical-align:top}
    .small{font-size:.9rem;color:var(--muted)} .celebrate{font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.02em;animation:pop .45s ease} @keyframes pop{0%{transform:scale(.95);opacity:0}70%{transform:scale(1.03);opacity:1}100%{transform:scale(1);opacity:1}}
    .section-title{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap}.hr{height:1px;background:var(--border);margin:12px 0}.footer-note{font-size:.9rem;color:#94a3b8}.badge-mastered{background:rgba(16,185,129,.18)}.badge-developing{background:rgba(96,165,250,.18)}.badge-gap{background:rgba(245,158,11,.18)}
  </style>

  <style id="gamehub-shared-identity-style">
    .gamehub-shared-identity { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:0.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap; margin: 0 0 0.75rem; padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.45); background: rgba(15,23,42,0.16); }
    .gamehub-shared-badge { font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.95; }
    .gamehub-practice-mode { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; opacity: 0.92; }
    .gamehub-back-link { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor; }
  </style>

</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="topbar">
        <div>
          <h1>Adaptive Learning V2 — Grades 1–6</h1>
          <p>Adaptive Math + English practice for grades 1–6, with skill snapshots, prerequisite support clues, and suggested next learning steps.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="pill">Version 2</span>
          <span class="pill">Local HTML</span>
          <span class="pill">No internet needed</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="startScreen" class="card">
      <h2>Start a Practice Session</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-4"><label>Learner name</label><input id="studentName" value="Demo Learner" /></div>
        <div class="col-4"><label>Subject</label><select id="subjectSelect"><option value="Mixed">Mixed</option><option value="Math">Math</option><option value="English">English</option></select></div>
        <div class="col-4"><label>Starting grade</label><select id="gradeSelect"><option value="1">1</option><option value="2">2</option><option value="3" selected>3</option><option value="4">4</option><option value="5">5</option><option value="6">6</option></select></div>
        <div class="col-4"><label>Number of questions</label><select id="questionCount"><option value="10">10</option><option value="15" selected>15</option><option value="20">20</option></select></div>
        <div class="col-4"><label>Session style</label><select id="modeSelect"><option value="diagnostic" selected>Balanced Practice</option><option value="practice">Guided Practice</option><option value="challenge">Challenge Practice</option></select></div>
        <div class="col-4"><label>Session goal</label><select id="goalSelect"><option value="balanced" selected>Balanced</option><option value="stretch">Stretch Upward</option><option value="support">Extra Support</option></select></div>
      </div>
      <div class="hr"></div>
      <h3>Grade 1 Adaptive V2 runtime (PR F)</h3>
      <div id="grade1V2Panel" class="mini"></div>
      <div class="hr"></div>
      <h3>What this practice version does</h3>
      <p class="small" id="modeNotice">Practice mode: Standard</p>
      <p>After the session, this version shares what felt strong, what needs more practice, the skill each question practiced, likely prerequisite supports, and a suggested next-step learning path.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:8px"><button id="startBtn">Start Session</button><button class="secondary" id="loadHistoryBtn">View History</button><button class="ghost" id="demoBtn">Load Demo Session</button></div>
    </div>

    <div id="quizScreen" class="card hidden">
      <div class="section-title"><div><h2 id="quizTitle">Question 1</h2><div id="quizMeta" class="small"></div></div><div><span id="levelBadge" class="pill"></span><span id="domainBadge" class="pill"></span></div></div>
      <div class="progress"><div id="progressBar"></div></div>
      <div style="margin-top:16px"><h3 id="promptText"></h3><div id="passageBox" class="mini hidden" style="margin:14px 0"></div><div id="choicesBox"></div></div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:12px"><button id="submitBtn">Check Answer</button><button class="secondary hidden" id="nextBtn">Next Question</button><button class="ghost" id="quitBtn">End Session Early</button></div>
      <div id="feedbackBox" class="feedback hidden"></div>
    </div>

    <div id="resultsScreen" class="hidden">
      <div class="card"><div class="section-title"><div><h2>Session Results</h2><p id="resultsIntro"></p></div><div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap"><button id="saveSessionBtn">Save Session</button><button class="secondary" id="newSessionBtn">Start New Session</button></div></div><div class="stats" id="statsGrid"></div></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Practice Snapshot + Learning Readiness</h2><p id="placementText"></p><div id="placementPills"></div><p class="small">Checkpoints help show what to practice next. They are not pass/fail labels.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Strengths</h2><div id="strengthsBox"></div></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Skills to Keep Building</h2><div id="developingBox"></div></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Priority Practice Needs + Likely Prerequisites</h2><div id="gapsBox"></div></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Recommended Next Learning Path</h2><div id="pathBox"></div></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>Question-by-Question Review</h2><div id="reviewBox"></div></div>
    </div>

    <div id="historyScreen" class="card hidden">
      <div class="section-title"><div><h2>Saved Session History</h2><p>Review practice snapshots over time using browser storage on this computer.</p></div><div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap"><button class="secondary" id="backHomeBtn">Back Home</button><button class="ghost" id="clearHistoryBtn">Clear History</button></div></div>
      <div id="historyBox"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer-note wrap">Tip: this file saves history only in this browser on this device.</div>
  </div>
<script src="/gamehub/shared-content-loader.js"></script>
<script src="/gamehub/gamehub-session-adapter.js"></script>
<script>
const CELEBRATIONS=["Yes! You spotted that.","Great job. You’re leveling up.","Nice work. That skill is getting stronger.","Boom. You got it right.","Beautiful thinking."];
const ENCOURAGEMENT=["Good try. Let’s break it down.","Not quite. Here’s what this question was asking.","You’re close. Let’s look at the skill underneath it.","This is a growth moment. Check the explanation below."];
const QUESTION_BANK=[
{id:"m6_1",subject:"Math",grade:6,domain:"Ratios & Rates",skill:"Find a unit rate",prerequisite_skill:"Divide whole numbers",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"If 4 apples cost $8, how much does 1 apple cost?",choices:["$1","$2","$3","$4"],correct_answer:"$2",correct_explanation:"A unit rate means the amount for 1 item. Divide 8 by 4 to get 2.",wrong_feedback:"Try dividing the total cost by the number of apples.",celebration_text:"Nice work! You found the cost per apple.",tags:["unit_rate","ratios"]},
{id:"m6_2",subject:"Math",grade:6,domain:"Fractions, Decimals & Percents",skill:"Convert fraction to decimal",prerequisite_skill:"Divide numerator by denominator",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is 3/4 written as a decimal?",choices:["0.25","0.5","0.75","1.25"],correct_answer:"0.75",correct_explanation:"3 ÷ 4 = 0.75, so 3/4 as a decimal is 0.75.",wrong_feedback:"A fraction can be turned into a decimal by dividing.",celebration_text:"Great conversion.",tags:["fractions","decimals"]},
{id:"m6_3",subject:"Math",grade:6,domain:"Expressions & Equations",skill:"Evaluate an expression",prerequisite_skill:"Order of operations basics",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is 3x + 2 when x = 4?",choices:["10","12","14","16"],correct_answer:"14",correct_explanation:"Substitute 4 for x: 3(4) + 2 = 12 + 2 = 14.",wrong_feedback:"Put the value in for x first, then solve.",celebration_text:"You substituted correctly.",tags:["expressions"]},
{id:"m6_4",subject:"Math",grade:6,domain:"Geometry",skill:"Find area of a rectangle",prerequisite_skill:"Multiply whole numbers",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"A rectangle is 7 units long and 3 units wide. What is its area?",choices:["10","20","21","24"],correct_answer:"21",correct_explanation:"Area of a rectangle is length × width. 7 × 3 = 21.",wrong_feedback:"Area uses multiplication, not addition.",celebration_text:"Area champion.",tags:["geometry","area"]},
{id:"m6_5",subject:"Math",grade:6,domain:"Statistics",skill:"Find the mean",prerequisite_skill:"Add and divide",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is the mean of 2, 4, 6, and 8?",choices:["4","5","6","7"],correct_answer:"5",correct_explanation:"Add the numbers: 2 + 4 + 6 + 8 = 20. Then divide by 4 to get 5.",wrong_feedback:"Mean means average: add, then divide by how many numbers there are.",celebration_text:"Nice averaging.",tags:["statistics","mean"]},
{id:"m7_1",subject:"Math",grade:7,domain:"Proportional Relationships",skill:"Solve a proportional relationship",prerequisite_skill:"Find a unit rate",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"If 5 notebooks cost $15, how much do 8 notebooks cost at the same rate?",choices:["$20","$22","$24","$26"],correct_answer:"$24",correct_explanation:"Each notebook costs $3 because 15 ÷ 5 = 3. Then 8 × 3 = 24.",wrong_feedback:"First find the cost of 1 notebook, then multiply.",celebration_text:"You scaled the ratio correctly.",tags:["proportions","unit_rate"]},
{id:"m7_2",subject:"Math",grade:7,domain:"Rational Numbers",skill:"Add integers",prerequisite_skill:"Understand positive and negative values",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is -7 + 12?",choices:["-19","-5","5","19"],correct_answer:"5",correct_explanation:"Starting at -7 and moving 12 to the right lands on 5.",wrong_feedback:"Think of a number line. Twelve positives cancel seven negatives and leave 5.",celebration_text:"Integer success.",tags:["integers"]},
{id:"m7_3",subject:"Math",grade:7,domain:"Expressions & Equations",skill:"Solve a two-step equation",prerequisite_skill:"Solve a one-step equation",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"Solve: 2x + 6 = 16",choices:["x = 4","x = 5","x = 8","x = 10"],correct_answer:"x = 5",correct_explanation:"Subtract 6 from both sides to get 2x = 10. Then divide by 2: x = 5.",wrong_feedback:"Undo addition first, then undo multiplication.",celebration_text:"Equation solved.",tags:["equations"]},
{id:"m7_4",subject:"Math",grade:7,domain:"Geometry",skill:"Find percent increase",prerequisite_skill:"Find percent of a number",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"A shirt cost $20 and now costs $25. What is the percent increase?",choices:["5%","20%","25%","125%"],correct_answer:"25%",correct_explanation:"The increase is 5. Divide 5 by the original 20: 5 ÷ 20 = 0.25 = 25%.",wrong_feedback:"Percent increase compares the change to the original amount.",celebration_text:"That percentage thinking was strong.",tags:["percent","change"]},
{id:"m7_5",subject:"Math",grade:7,domain:"Probability & Statistics",skill:"Find experimental probability",prerequisite_skill:"Understand part over total",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"A coin lands on heads 18 times in 30 flips. What is the experimental probability of heads?",choices:["3/5","5/3","18/12","1/2"],correct_answer:"3/5",correct_explanation:"Experimental probability is successes over total trials: 18/30, which simplifies to 3/5.",wrong_feedback:"Put heads over total flips, then simplify.",celebration_text:"Nice probability reasoning.",tags:["probability"]},
{id:"m8_1",subject:"Math",grade:8,domain:"Linear Relationships",skill:"Find slope from points",prerequisite_skill:"Subtract integers",difficulty:3,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is the slope of the line through (1, 2) and (5, 10)?",choices:["1","2","4","8"],correct_answer:"2",correct_explanation:"Slope = rise/run = (10 - 2) / (5 - 1) = 8/4 = 2.",wrong_feedback:"Use change in y over change in x.",celebration_text:"Strong slope work.",tags:["slope","linear"]},
{id:"m8_2",subject:"Math",grade:8,domain:"Functions",skill:"Identify a function rule",prerequisite_skill:"Recognize input-output patterns",difficulty:3,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"A function table shows x=1 gives y=4, x=2 gives y=7, x=3 gives y=10. Which rule fits?",choices:["y = x + 3","y = 3x + 1","y = 4x","y = 2x + 2"],correct_answer:"y = 3x + 1",correct_explanation:"Check the pattern: when x=1, y=4; when x=2, y=7; when x=3, y=10. The rule y = 3x + 1 works for all three.",wrong_feedback:"Test each rule with all the input-output pairs.",celebration_text:"Pattern detective.",tags:["functions"]},
{id:"m8_3",subject:"Math",grade:8,domain:"Exponents & Scientific Notation",skill:"Evaluate an exponent",prerequisite_skill:"Multiply repeated factors",difficulty:3,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What is 2^4?",choices:["6","8","12","16"],correct_answer:"16",correct_explanation:"2^4 means 2 × 2 × 2 × 2 = 16.",wrong_feedback:"An exponent means repeated multiplication.",celebration_text:"Exponent power.",tags:["exponents"]},
{id:"m8_4",subject:"Math",grade:8,domain:"Geometry",skill:"Understand transformations",prerequisite_skill:"Identify coordinate points",difficulty:3,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"What happens to point (3, -2) after a reflection across the x-axis?",choices:["(-3, -2)","(3, 2)","(-3, 2)","(2, 3)"],correct_answer:"(3, 2)",correct_explanation:"A reflection across the x-axis keeps x the same and changes the sign of y.",wrong_feedback:"Only the y-value changes sign for an x-axis reflection.",celebration_text:"Transformation complete.",tags:["geometry","transformations"]},
{id:"m8_5",subject:"Math",grade:8,domain:"Systems Foundations",skill:"Check a solution to a linear equation",prerequisite_skill:"Substitute into equations",difficulty:3,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"Does x = 3 make 4x - 5 = 7 true?",choices:["Yes","No"],correct_answer:"Yes",correct_explanation:"Substitute 3: 4(3) - 5 = 12 - 5 = 7, so yes.",wrong_feedback:"Plug the value in and compare both sides.",celebration_text:"You verified it correctly.",tags:["algebra"]},
{id:"e6_1",subject:"English",grade:6,domain:"Main Idea",skill:"Identify the main idea",prerequisite_skill:"Recognize important details",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"Maya practiced piano every day after school. At first, she struggled to keep a steady rhythm. After several weeks, she could play her song smoothly at the recital.",prompt:"What is the main idea of the passage?",choices:["Maya dislikes music class.","Maya improved by practicing regularly.","Recitals are hard for all students.","Piano songs should be short."],correct_answer:"Maya improved by practicing regularly.",correct_explanation:"The details all show that Maya practiced often and became better over time.",wrong_feedback:"Look for the idea that connects the whole passage.",celebration_text:"You found the big idea.",tags:["reading","main_idea"]},
{id:"e6_2",subject:"English",grade:6,domain:"Vocabulary in Context",skill:"Use context clues",prerequisite_skill:"Read surrounding sentences closely",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"The desert was arid, with cracked ground and almost no rain for months.",prompt:"What does arid most likely mean?",choices:["crowded","dry","cold","soft"],correct_answer:"dry",correct_explanation:"The clues 'cracked ground' and 'almost no rain' show that arid means dry.",wrong_feedback:"Use the words around the unfamiliar word as clues.",celebration_text:"Context clue win.",tags:["vocabulary"]},
{id:"e6_3",subject:"English",grade:6,domain:"Grammar",skill:"Choose the correct pronoun",prerequisite_skill:"Match pronouns to nouns",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"Choose the correct sentence.",choices:["The learner and me went to the library.","The learner and I went to the library.","Me and the learner went to the library.","The learner and myself went to the library."],correct_answer:"The learner and I went to the library.",correct_explanation:"When the pronoun is part of the subject, use I, not me.",wrong_feedback:"Remove the other person to test it: 'I went to the library' sounds correct.",celebration_text:"Grammar glow-up.",tags:["grammar","pronouns"]},
{id:"e6_4",subject:"English",grade:6,domain:"Sentence Structure",skill:"Identify a complete sentence",prerequisite_skill:"Know subject and predicate",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"Which choice is a complete sentence?",choices:["Running through the park.","Because the rain stopped.","The team won the game.","After school on Tuesday."],correct_answer:"The team won the game.",correct_explanation:"A complete sentence has a subject and a complete thought. 'The team won the game' does both.",wrong_feedback:"A sentence needs a who or what plus a complete thought.",celebration_text:"Sentence complete.",tags:["sentence_structure"]},
{id:"e6_5",subject:"English",grade:6,domain:"Text Evidence",skill:"Use evidence from a text",prerequisite_skill:"Identify supporting details",difficulty:1,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"Lena wore boots, a thick coat, gloves, and a scarf before stepping outside. She smiled when she saw snow covering the sidewalk.",prompt:"Which detail best shows that the weather is cold?",choices:["Lena smiled.","She stepped outside.","She wore boots, gloves, and a scarf.","The sidewalk was outside."],correct_answer:"She wore boots, gloves, and a scarf.",correct_explanation:"Those clothing details are evidence that the weather is cold.",wrong_feedback:"Text evidence means choosing the detail that proves the idea.",celebration_text:"Evidence found.",tags:["text_evidence"]},
{id:"e7_1",subject:"English",grade:7,domain:"Inference",skill:"Make an inference",prerequisite_skill:"Notice important details",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"Jordan kept glancing at the clock and tapping his pencil. When his name was finally called, he took a deep breath before walking to the front of the room.",prompt:"What can the reader infer about Jordan?",choices:["He is bored with class.","He is nervous about presenting.","He wants to leave school early.","He forgot his pencil."],correct_answer:"He is nervous about presenting.",correct_explanation:"Glancing at the clock, tapping a pencil, and taking a deep breath suggest nervousness.",wrong_feedback:"An inference is based on clues, not directly stated facts.",celebration_text:"Smart inference.",tags:["inference"]},
{id:"e7_2",subject:"English",grade:7,domain:"Author's Purpose",skill:"Identify author’s purpose",prerequisite_skill:"Recognize text features and tone",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"Washing your reusable water bottle each day can reduce germs and keep the bottle smelling fresh. Use warm water, soap, and a bottle brush to clean it well.",prompt:"What is the author's main purpose?",choices:["to entertain","to persuade","to inform/instruct","to describe a vacation"],correct_answer:"to inform/instruct",correct_explanation:"The passage gives helpful information and directions about cleaning a water bottle.",wrong_feedback:"Ask: is the author trying to teach, entertain, persuade, or describe?",celebration_text:"Purpose identified.",tags:["authors_purpose"]},
{id:"e7_3",subject:"English",grade:7,domain:"Grammar",skill:"Choose correct verb tense",prerequisite_skill:"Recognize past, present, and future tense",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",prompt:"Choose the correct sentence.",choices:["Yesterday, the learner go to the store.","Yesterday, the learner goes to the store.","Yesterday, the learner went to the store.","Yesterday, the learner going to the store."],correct_answer:"Yesterday, the learner went to the store.",correct_explanation:"Yesterday signals past tense, so went is correct.",wrong_feedback:"Time words like yesterday help you choose the correct tense.",celebration_text:"Tense locked in.",tags:["grammar","verb_tense"]},
{id:"e7_4",subject:"English",grade:7,domain:"Theme",skill:"Identify theme",prerequisite_skill:"Determine main idea",difficulty:2,question_type:"multiple_choice",passage:"When Tasha first joined the soccer team, she rarely spoke. Over time, her teammates encouraged her, and she learned to trust them. By the last game, she was leading cheers from the bench.",prompt:"Which theme best fits the passage?",choices:["Winning is everything.","Team support can build confidence.","Sports are easy to learn.","Silence is better than speaking."],correct_answer:"Team support can build confidence.",correct_explanation:"The story shows that encouragement from others helped Tasha become more confident.",wrong_feedback:"A theme is a message or lesson, not just one event from the story.",celebration_text:"Theme tracker.",tags:["theme"]},
